         <abstract id="aspace_f23a7db052e7aca40c3d7d061c89697d">The materials consist of photographs of buildings constructed for the Yale bicentennial. The bulk of the collection documents the University Dining Hall and Woolsey Hall. One photograph documents construction in 1901.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <odd id="aspace_8bb7a527b18df34780a6bb37290fbe24">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 46-B (YRG 46-B), Records and materials documenting individual Yale buildings, facilities, and grounds.</p>  
      </odd>
      <prefercite id="aspace_af10238c6b20f909c93ce0e1f3d8f0a4">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Buildings Constructed for Yale University's Bicentennial Photographs (RU 697). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_5bb1da88602a1f493b7e58bcba4f9aea">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_618a5a9beb38444d2d1d3467a3aef066">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by topic.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_8115fdc553bccb2d5e527ebe0c444337">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of photographs of buildings constructed for the Yale bicentennial. The bulk of the collection documents the University Dining Hall and Woolsey Hall. One photograph documents construction in 1901.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
  
